'''Cheryl Shuman''' is the founder of the [[Beverly Hills Cannabis Club]].
==Early life== Shuman was born in [[Buena Vista, Scioto County, Ohio|Buena Vista, Ohio]],<ref name="Ross">{{cite news|last1=Ross|first1=Theodore|title=The Cannabis Queen of Beverly Hills|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/11/magazine/the-cannabis-queen-of-beverly-hills.html|accessdate=February 26, 2018|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=January 9, 2015}}</ref> and raised in [[Portsmouth, Ohio]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.portsmouth-dailytimes.com/news/19102/how-marijuana-saved-the-cannabis-queen|title=How marijuana saved the ‘Cannabis Queen'|work=Portsmouth Daily Times|date=September 18, 2017|accessdate=February 26, 2018}}</ref>
==Cannabis== Shuman has used cannabis since 1996, when she founded the Beverly Hills Cannabis Club. In 2015, ''[[LA Weekly]]'' referred to her as the "Martha Stewart of Marijuana" and ''[[The New York Times]]''{{'}} Theodore Ross called her the "Cannabis Queen of Beverly Hills".<ref name=Ross/><ref name="Martha">{{cite news|last=Denman-Underhill|first=Lori|title=The "Martha Stewart of Marijuana" Helps Women Get Into the Weed Business|url=http://www.laweekly.com/music/the-martha-stewart-of-marijuana-helps-women-get-into-the-weed-business-5536188|accessdate=February 26, 2018|work=[[LA Weekly]]|date=May 5, 2015|publisher=[[Voice Media Group]]|issn=0192-1940}}</ref>
