'''Mark J. Berg''' is an American politician from [[Virginia]]. A member of the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]], he was a member of the [[Virginia House of Delegates]] for one term, representing the 29th district. In the 2013 elections, he defeated the incumbent Republican and then defeated the Independent opponent Larry Yates. A retired doctor, Berg is affiliated with the [[Tea Party movement]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nvdaily.com/news/2013/11/berg-wins-race-for-29th-district-house-delegate/ |title=Berg wins race for 29th district House delegate |first=Joe |last=Beck |newspaper=The Northern Virginia Daily |date=November 5, 2013 |accessdate=January 17, 2016}}</ref> He himself was defeated in a primary challenge in the 2015 elections, by attorney [[Chris Collins (Virginia politician)|Chris Collins]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Charlip |first=Rachel |date=June 9, 2015 |title=Chris Collins wins VA's House of Delegates 29th district seat |url=http://www.your4state.com/news/news/chris-collins-wins-vas-house-of-delegates-29th-district-seat |newspaper=WHAG-TV |location= |access-date=January 17, 2016 }}</ref>
